WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.000
Under the Moon by Rowena Akanyemi.

00:09.000 --> 00:11.000
Chapter 1

00:11.000 --> 00:13.000
AOL

00:13.000 --> 00:17.000
500km over Europe.

00:17.000 --> 00:23.000
Ship OM45 moved north.

00:23.000 --> 00:29.000
In a room at the back of the ship, Kia watched the numbers

00:29.000 --> 00:34.000
on the computer in front of him.

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
Time for dinner?

00:36.000 --> 00:39.000
Rilla said.

00:39.000 --> 00:42.000
The numbers changed quickly.

00:42.000 --> 00:47.000
And Kia's eyes didn't move.

00:47.000 --> 00:52.000
Rilla went across the room to his table.

00:52.000 --> 00:57.000
She began to watch the numbers too.

00:57.000 --> 01:00.000
What's wrong with a satellite?

01:00.000 --> 01:02.000
She asked.

01:02.000 --> 01:07.000
She was a beautiful girl, about twenty years old,

01:07.000 --> 01:12.000
with long black hair and big eyes.

01:12.000 --> 01:15.000
Nothing's wrong with a satellite.

01:15.000 --> 01:18.000
Kia answered quietly.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
It's the AOL.

01:22.000 --> 01:28.000
He began to write the numbers in the book on his table.

01:28.000 --> 01:33.000
Suddenly, the numbers stopped changing.

01:33.000 --> 01:36.000
Kia looked at Rilla.

01:36.000 --> 01:40.000
Over Europe, he said.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.000
It's happening.

01:42.000 --> 01:46.000
The AOL is breaking up.

01:46.000 --> 01:51.000
There are big holes in the AOL, and they're getting bigger.

01:51.000 --> 01:54.000
You're right.

01:54.000 --> 02:00.000
Shall we see Captain Seru now, before dinner?

02:00.000 --> 02:03.000
Kia stood up.

02:03.000 --> 02:09.000
He was nearly two meters tall, with dark eyes and hair.

02:09.000 --> 02:11.000
Yes, come on.

02:11.000 --> 02:14.000
He said.

02:14.000 --> 02:19.000
Quickly, they went to Captain Seru's room.

02:19.000 --> 02:22.000
They waited at the door.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
Come in.

02:24.000 --> 02:27.000
Captain Seru called.

02:27.000 --> 02:31.000
She was a little woman with a fat face.

02:31.000 --> 02:33.000
Come in.

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
Would you like a drink?

02:36.000 --> 02:38.000
No, thank you.

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
Kia answered.

02:40.000 --> 02:44.000
I'd like you to look at these numbers.

02:44.000 --> 02:49.000
Kia gave Captain Seru his book.

02:49.000 --> 02:53.000
Captain Seru looked at the numbers.

02:53.000 --> 02:58.000
Suddenly, her face changed.

02:58.000 --> 03:01.000
No, no, she said.

03:01.000 --> 03:03.000
I don't want to talk.

03:03.000 --> 03:06.000
It's late, and I'm tired.

03:06.000 --> 03:10.000
Sit down and have a drink.

03:10.000 --> 03:14.000
Kia and Rila sat down.

03:14.000 --> 03:19.000
There was a big window in Captain Seru's room.

03:19.000 --> 03:25.000
Kia looked out of the window at the dark sky.

03:25.000 --> 03:28.000
He saw the moon.

03:28.000 --> 03:33.000
It was cold and white in the dark sky.

03:33.000 --> 03:37.000
Captain Seru, he began.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
It's important.

03:39.000 --> 03:43.000
Look at those numbers carefully.

03:43.000 --> 03:48.000
The AOL is beginning to stop.

03:48.000 --> 03:54.000
Captain Seru stood up and put her hands in her pockets.

03:54.000 --> 04:00.000
She went to the window and looked at the sky.

04:00.000 --> 04:05.000
Three hundred years ago, Earth nearly died.

04:05.000 --> 04:08.000
Rila said.

04:08.000 --> 04:12.000
Earth stopped dying because of the AOL.

04:12.000 --> 04:19.000
But now, over Europe, the AOL is breaking up.

04:19.000 --> 04:24.000
We would like you to talk to Earth Commander.

04:24.000 --> 04:29.000
Captain Seru did not move.

04:29.000 --> 04:31.000
Do you remember a die?

04:31.000 --> 04:33.000
She asked.

04:33.000 --> 04:37.000
She didn't wait for an answer.

04:37.000 --> 04:42.000
I was on his ship two years ago.

04:42.000 --> 04:50.000
One evening, the satellite gave us interesting numbers about the AOL.

04:50.000 --> 04:55.000
We went back to Earth and saw Earth Commander.

04:55.000 --> 04:59.000
Captain Seru stopped speaking.

04:59.000 --> 05:03.000
Rila looked at Kia.

05:03.000 --> 05:08.000
And then, she asked Captain Seru.

05:08.000 --> 05:10.000
Gog was angry.

05:10.000 --> 05:13.000
Very angry.

05:13.000 --> 05:16.000
Captain Seru said.

05:16.000 --> 05:21.000
In the end, he sent a die to the moon.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.000
A die is there now.

05:23.000 --> 05:29.000
Commander of the moon colony under the moon.

05:29.000 --> 05:34.000
Kia waited for a second or two.

05:34.000 --> 05:37.000
I know about a die.

05:37.000 --> 05:41.000
But we need to talk to Earth Commander again.

05:41.000 --> 05:45.000
These numbers are worse.

05:45.000 --> 05:49.000
Captain Seru's face went red.

05:49.000 --> 05:52.000
You don't understand.

05:52.000 --> 05:55.000
I'm not going to talk to Gog.

05:55.000 --> 06:02.000
Last time, he sent me to our weather ship in the Antarctic.

06:02.000 --> 06:07.000
This is my first ship for two years.

06:07.000 --> 06:12.000
And Captain Seru began drinking.

06:12.000 --> 06:15.000
Kia stood up.

06:15.000 --> 06:19.000
Thank you, Captain Seru.

06:19.000 --> 06:23.000
Captain Seru said nothing.

06:23.000 --> 06:31.000
Kia and Rila left the room and walked slowly downstairs.

06:31.000 --> 06:35.000
The ship was dark and quiet.

06:35.000 --> 06:42.000
It was eight o'clock and everybody was at dinner.

06:42.000 --> 06:45.000
What are we going to do next?

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
Rila asked.

06:48.000 --> 06:51.000
I need to talk to a die.

06:51.000 --> 06:53.000
Kia said.

06:53.000 --> 06:57.000
Okay, talk to a die.

06:57.000 --> 07:00.000
But he's far away on the moon colony.

07:00.000 --> 07:03.000
Rila said.

07:03.000 --> 07:07.000
Let's visit Commander Zadak.

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
Zadak.

07:09.000 --> 07:12.000
Commander of Australia.

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
He's famous.

07:14.000 --> 07:16.000
Yes.

07:16.000 --> 07:19.000
He's my father's friend.

07:19.000 --> 07:24.000
He worked with my father in Brazil ten years ago.

07:24.000 --> 07:28.000
Perhaps he can help us.

07:28.000 --> 07:31.000
Kia smiled.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
Good.

07:33.000 --> 07:36.000
We return to Earth next week.

07:36.000 --> 07:39.000
I can phone a die from Kisangani.

07:39.000 --> 07:42.000
And then we can go to Australia.

07:42.000 --> 07:46.000
But now I'm hungry.

07:46.000 --> 07:49.000
Let's get some dinner.

08:07.000 --> 08:09.000
Chapter Two.

08:09.000 --> 08:14.000
Visit to Australia.

08:14.000 --> 08:19.000
On Friday, after three weeks in space,

08:19.000 --> 08:26.000
Kia and Rila finished work and left ship OM45

08:26.000 --> 08:31.000
on a space plane to Kisangani.

08:31.000 --> 08:33.000
Kia phoned a die.

08:33.000 --> 08:39.000
And Rila phoned Commander Zadak in Australia.

08:39.000 --> 08:46.000
The next morning, they took an aeroplane to Sydney.

08:46.000 --> 08:53.000
A taxi took them from the airport to Commander Zadak's office,

08:53.000 --> 08:58.000
some kilometers north of Sydney.

08:58.000 --> 09:00.000
Wait for us here.

09:00.000 --> 09:03.000
Kia said to the taxi driver.

09:03.000 --> 09:07.000
Kia and Rila walked to the gate.

09:07.000 --> 09:12.000
About ten guards stood in front of the gate.

09:12.000 --> 09:17.000
Across the road, a train waited.

09:17.000 --> 09:21.000
Rila OM45.

09:21.000 --> 09:22.000
Rila said,

09:22.000 --> 09:27.000
to see Commander Zadak at 430.

09:27.000 --> 09:30.000
Let me call the commander's office.

09:30.000 --> 09:33.000
The guard said.

09:33.000 --> 09:37.000
Kia and Rila waited.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
It was hot.

09:39.000 --> 09:42.000
And Kia began to feel thirsty.

09:42.000 --> 09:45.000
The guard came back.

09:45.000 --> 09:48.000
I'm sorry, he said.

09:48.000 --> 09:51.000
The commander can't see you.

09:51.000 --> 09:55.000
But I talked to the commander yesterday.

09:55.000 --> 09:57.000
Rila said.

09:57.000 --> 10:01.000
He wanted to see us at 430.

10:01.000 --> 10:05.000
The commander is leaving on the train in three minutes.

10:05.000 --> 10:08.000
The guard said.

10:08.000 --> 10:11.000
Can we wait and see him here?

10:11.000 --> 10:13.000
Kia asked.

10:13.000 --> 10:14.000
No.

10:14.000 --> 10:17.000
The guard shouted.

10:17.000 --> 10:20.000
Get out of here.

10:20.000 --> 10:24.000
Kia and Rila walked back to the taxi.

10:24.000 --> 10:26.000
Where's the driver?

10:26.000 --> 10:28.000
Kia asked.

10:28.000 --> 10:29.000
Look!

10:29.000 --> 10:32.000
He's sitting by that wall.

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
Rila said.

10:34.000 --> 10:39.000
Just then, Commander Zadak came out of the gate.

10:39.000 --> 10:47.000
He was a very tall, big man with blue eyes and a lot of white hair.

10:47.000 --> 10:55.000
Two guards marched in front of him and two guards marched behind him.

10:55.000 --> 10:59.000
They all carried guns.

10:59.000 --> 11:03.000
There he is, Rila cried.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.000
Commander!

11:05.000 --> 11:10.000
And she began to run along the road to him.

11:10.000 --> 11:13.000
Commander Zadak did not stop.

11:13.000 --> 11:19.000
A guard opened the door of the train and the commander got in.

11:19.000 --> 11:23.000
Slowly the train began to move.

11:23.000 --> 11:28.000
Kia ran to the taxi and jumped in.

11:28.000 --> 11:33.000
Then he drove the taxi fast down the road.

11:33.000 --> 11:39.000
The taxi driver saw him and ran after him.

11:39.000 --> 11:44.000
The train began to move faster.

11:44.000 --> 11:50.000
Suddenly Kia drove the taxi off the road.

11:50.000 --> 11:55.000
He drove in front of the train and stopped.

11:55.000 --> 11:59.000
The train came nearer.

11:59.000 --> 12:02.000
And then the train stopped.

12:02.000 --> 12:05.000
Very near the taxi.

12:05.000 --> 12:09.000
And some guards jumped off.

12:09.000 --> 12:15.000
Kia opened the door and got out of the taxi.

12:15.000 --> 12:20.000
Put up your hands, the guards shouted.

12:20.000 --> 12:24.000
Two of the guards began to hit Kia.

12:24.000 --> 12:28.000
Stop that, someone shouted.

12:28.000 --> 12:31.000
Bring him over here.

12:31.000 --> 12:35.000
It was Commander Zadak.

12:35.000 --> 12:39.000
Kia stood in front of the commander.

12:39.000 --> 12:42.000
Just then Rila arrived.

12:42.000 --> 12:45.000
Oh, it's you.

12:45.000 --> 12:48.000
Commander Zadak said.

12:48.000 --> 12:50.000
He did not smile.

12:50.000 --> 12:55.000
Rila, your father's going to be angry.

12:55.000 --> 12:59.000
We want to talk to you, Commander.

12:59.000 --> 13:03.000
Commander Zadak said, it's very important.

13:03.000 --> 13:07.000
Very well, I'm listening.

13:07.000 --> 13:10.000
Kia began to talk.

13:10.000 --> 13:16.000
Two years ago, Adai told you about the holes in the AOL.

13:16.000 --> 13:19.000
Now they are worse.

13:19.000 --> 13:23.000
The AOL is breaking up over Europe.

13:23.000 --> 13:28.000
Please look at these numbers and this satellite picture.

13:28.000 --> 13:32.000
He gave his book to Commander Zadak

13:32.000 --> 13:36.000
and the commander looked at the numbers.

13:36.000 --> 13:39.000
It's important, Commander.

13:39.000 --> 13:46.000
Kia said, in ten years, Earth is going to die.

13:46.000 --> 13:50.000
You stop my train because of this?

13:50.000 --> 13:53.000
Commander Zadak asked.

13:53.000 --> 13:59.000
Two years ago, Adai talked to me about the AOL.

13:59.000 --> 14:02.000
Then he talked to Earth Commander.

14:02.000 --> 14:04.000
And what happened?

14:04.000 --> 14:06.000
Where is Adai now?

14:06.000 --> 14:11.000
Is the moon colony helping the AOL?

14:11.000 --> 14:16.000
We know about Adai, Commander, Rila said.

14:16.000 --> 14:21.000
But someone needs to talk to Earth Commander again.

14:21.000 --> 14:24.000
I'm going to talk to Gog about rain.

14:24.000 --> 14:26.000
I can tell you that.

14:26.000 --> 14:29.000
Earth needs rain.

14:29.000 --> 14:32.000
There was no rain last winter.

14:32.000 --> 14:38.000
Half of Australia has no water and my trees here are dying.

14:38.000 --> 14:42.000
Without rain, many people are going to die.

14:42.000 --> 14:46.000
Is Gog going to understand that?

14:46.000 --> 14:49.000
I don't know.

14:49.000 --> 14:53.000
Commander Zadak began to walk back to his train.

14:53.000 --> 14:55.000
Move that taxi.

14:55.000 --> 14:58.000
He called to his guards.

14:58.000 --> 15:01.000
Some guards moved the taxi back to the road,

15:01.000 --> 15:05.000
and then they jumped onto the train again.

15:05.000 --> 15:08.000
The train began to move.

15:08.000 --> 15:12.000
Okay, the taxi driver shouted.

15:12.000 --> 15:15.000
What are you going to do next?

15:15.000 --> 15:18.000
Drive my taxi into the river?

15:18.000 --> 15:20.000
Kia smiled.

15:20.000 --> 15:26.000
He took some money from his pocket and gave it to the taxi driver.

15:26.000 --> 15:29.000
The taxi driver looked at the money.

15:29.000 --> 15:33.000
Okay, okay, he said.

15:33.000 --> 15:35.000
Where now?

15:35.000 --> 15:37.000
Back to the airport?

15:37.000 --> 15:40.000
Kia took Rila's hand.

15:40.000 --> 15:42.000
Yes, he said.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.000
Let's get back to Kisangani.

15:44.000 --> 15:47.000
We can phone Adai again tomorrow.

15:47.000 --> 16:06.000
MUSIC

16:06.000 --> 16:08.000
Chapter 3

16:08.000 --> 16:11.000
Earth Commander

16:11.000 --> 16:15.000
The next day in Kisangani

16:15.000 --> 16:22.000
Kia and Rila waited quietly in an office in Gog's house.

16:22.000 --> 16:27.000
Suddenly, Commander Zadak came into the office

16:27.000 --> 16:33.000
and gave some letters to the man behind the table.

16:33.000 --> 16:39.000
He saw the two young people and stopped in front of them.

16:39.000 --> 16:42.000
You again, he said.

16:42.000 --> 16:45.000
What are you doing here?

16:45.000 --> 16:48.000
Kia stood up.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.000
Good morning, Commander.

16:50.000 --> 16:55.000
We're here because we want to see Earth Commander.

16:55.000 --> 17:02.000
I saw Earth Commander some minutes ago and talked to him about rain.

17:02.000 --> 17:07.000
Zadak said quietly, but he didn't listen.

17:07.000 --> 17:11.000
Your Captain Seru was here earlier this morning

17:11.000 --> 17:16.000
and began to tell him about the holes in the AOL.

17:16.000 --> 17:21.000
But Gog doesn't want to hear about our planet.

17:21.000 --> 17:24.000
He's always talking about Mars.

17:24.000 --> 17:29.000
In the end, he's going to destroy Earth.

17:29.000 --> 17:34.000
Please help us, Rila cried.

17:34.000 --> 17:37.000
Come and see Gog with us.

17:37.000 --> 17:39.000
No.

17:39.000 --> 17:45.000
Zadak looked at Kia and then at Rila with his blue eyes.

17:45.000 --> 17:48.000
I'm not talking to Gog again.

17:48.000 --> 17:53.000
And you, Gog isn't going to listen to you.

17:53.000 --> 17:58.000
Be careful and good luck.

17:58.000 --> 18:05.000
Commander Zadak opened the door and left the office.

18:05.000 --> 18:08.000
Rila looked at Kia.

18:08.000 --> 18:11.000
Earth Commander is a difficult man.

18:11.000 --> 18:14.000
I don't understand him.

18:14.000 --> 18:17.000
Everyone is afraid of him.

18:17.000 --> 18:19.000
Kia said.

18:19.000 --> 18:23.000
And Commander Zadak isn't going to help us.

18:23.000 --> 18:26.000
Kia and Rila waited.

18:26.000 --> 18:29.000
They waited and waited.

18:29.000 --> 18:35.000
At nearly twelve o'clock, a guard came into the office.

18:35.000 --> 18:39.000
Come, he said.

18:39.000 --> 18:43.000
Kia and Rila went with the guard.

18:43.000 --> 18:50.000
The house was big and old with big windows and many doors.

18:50.000 --> 18:55.000
The guard went downstairs and opened one of the doors.

18:55.000 --> 18:59.000
There was nobody in the room.

18:59.000 --> 19:05.000
Wait here, the guard said, and left.

19:05.000 --> 19:11.000
Kia and Rila sat down on the expensive green and black chairs

19:11.000 --> 19:15.000
and looked at the expensive flowers on the tables.

19:15.000 --> 19:19.000
There were no windows in this room.

19:19.000 --> 19:26.000
Suddenly, the door opened and a tall fat woman came in.

19:26.000 --> 19:31.000
Her name was Belle and she was Gog's wife.

19:31.000 --> 19:39.000
She had a lot of long red hair and she wore an expensive blue dress.

19:39.000 --> 19:42.000
Belle liked expensive things.

19:42.000 --> 19:45.000
She carried a cat.

19:45.000 --> 19:49.000
The cat was black and white.

19:49.000 --> 19:54.000
Half its face was black and half was white.

19:54.000 --> 20:00.000
Half its body was black and half was white.

20:00.000 --> 20:02.000
Why are you here?

20:02.000 --> 20:06.000
Why do you want to see Earth, Commander?

20:06.000 --> 20:08.000
She asked.

20:08.000 --> 20:10.000
Rila stood up.

20:10.000 --> 20:12.000
How do you do?

20:12.000 --> 20:14.000
She said.

20:14.000 --> 20:19.000
We want to talk to Earth, Commander, about the AOL.

20:19.000 --> 20:23.000
We have new numbers from the satellite.

20:23.000 --> 20:26.000
Belle's face was red.

20:26.000 --> 20:35.000
The AOL Earth, Commander, knows about the AOL and he is the best man.

20:35.000 --> 20:40.000
Excuse me, Kia said quietly.

20:40.000 --> 20:44.000
We want to help Earth, Commander.

20:44.000 --> 20:47.000
Belle began to laugh.

20:47.000 --> 20:50.000
Help! You!

20:50.000 --> 20:54.000
The cat jumped down and walked across the room.

20:54.000 --> 20:56.000
How can you help?

20:56.000 --> 20:59.000
Why can't you understand?

20:59.000 --> 21:04.000
Listen, Earth, Commander is working on the spaceship for Mars.

21:04.000 --> 21:08.000
It's difficult and expensive work.

21:08.000 --> 21:14.000
The cat jumped onto Rila's chair and looked at her with its yellow eyes.

21:14.000 --> 21:24.000
Two years ago, a guy wanted more money for the AOL and Earth, Commander, sent him to the colony under the moon.

21:24.000 --> 21:27.000
Now you're talking about the AOL.

21:27.000 --> 21:31.000
Do you want to go to the moon too?

21:31.000 --> 21:36.000
The door opened again and a different guard came in.

21:36.000 --> 21:40.000
Excuse me, Earth, Commander, is ready now.

21:40.000 --> 21:42.000
Belle stood up.

21:42.000 --> 21:45.000
You can see Earth, Commander, now.

21:45.000 --> 21:47.000
She said coldly.

21:47.000 --> 21:52.000
But you're going to be sorry.

21:52.000 --> 21:55.000
The guard opened a different door.

21:55.000 --> 22:03.000
And Belle and the cat went into a beautiful room with expensive, very old tables and chairs.

22:03.000 --> 22:07.000
Rila and Keir went in behind them.

22:07.000 --> 22:12.000
There were no windows in the room but a lot of pictures.

22:12.000 --> 22:20.000
There was Gog, the richest man on Earth and the worst man on Earth.

22:20.000 --> 22:25.000
He was tall and fat and without much hair.

22:26.000 --> 22:33.000
He sat behind a big table with a television, three computers and five telephones.

22:33.000 --> 22:39.000
He watched the television and didn't look at Keir or Rila.

22:39.000 --> 22:47.000
Two guards with guns stood behind him and two more guards stood near the door.

22:48.000 --> 22:51.000
Here they are, Belle said.

22:51.000 --> 22:53.000
They aren't friends.

22:53.000 --> 22:55.000
Oh no.

22:55.000 --> 22:59.000
They want to talk about the AOL, of course.

22:59.000 --> 23:02.000
No one understands about Mars.

23:02.000 --> 23:03.000
That's all right.

23:03.000 --> 23:05.000
That's all the right.

23:05.000 --> 23:07.000
Gog said quickly.

23:07.000 --> 23:09.000
And then he looked up.

23:09.000 --> 23:13.000
First at Rila and then at Keir.

23:13.000 --> 23:16.000
His eyes were cold and green.

23:16.000 --> 23:19.000
I know about you too.

23:19.000 --> 23:24.000
He said, your captain told me about you.

23:24.000 --> 23:28.000
Your famous two children.

23:28.000 --> 23:31.000
You want to help Planet Earth.

23:31.000 --> 23:33.000
Is that right?

23:33.000 --> 23:35.000
He waited.

23:35.000 --> 23:42.000
The cat jumped onto his table and sat down in front of the television.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.000
Yes, Commander.

23:45.000 --> 23:46.000
Keir began.

23:46.000 --> 23:50.000
The AOL is breaking up.

23:50.000 --> 23:51.000
When?

23:51.000 --> 23:52.000
Tonight?

23:52.000 --> 23:53.000
Tomorrow?

23:53.000 --> 23:55.000
Gog said angrily.

23:55.000 --> 24:00.000
I heard this old story two years ago from Adai.

24:00.000 --> 24:04.000
Everyone comes here and wants money.

24:04.000 --> 24:06.000
Money for the AOL.

24:06.000 --> 24:08.000
Money for rain.

24:08.000 --> 24:11.000
Money for the moon colony.

24:11.000 --> 24:14.000
But I am Earth Commander.

24:14.000 --> 24:17.000
And you are nobody.

24:17.000 --> 24:20.000
I know about the AOL.

24:20.000 --> 24:25.000
And the AOL is good for a hundred years.

24:25.000 --> 24:27.000
But the satellite.

24:27.000 --> 24:29.000
Keir began again.

24:29.000 --> 24:31.000
Big quiet.

24:31.000 --> 24:32.000
Gog cried.

24:32.000 --> 24:35.000
I am Earth Commander.

24:35.000 --> 24:39.000
I'm not going to give money for the AOL.

24:39.000 --> 24:41.000
Or for rain.

24:41.000 --> 24:44.000
Or for the moon.

24:44.000 --> 24:47.000
Gog looked at the guards near the door.

24:47.000 --> 24:49.000
Take them.

24:49.000 --> 24:51.000
Take them away.

24:51.000 --> 24:55.000
I don't want to hear them.

24:55.000 --> 24:59.000
The guards moved behind Keir and Rilla.

24:59.000 --> 25:02.000
And Bell began to laugh.

25:02.000 --> 25:04.000
Goodbye.

25:04.000 --> 25:08.000
She said, you're not going to the moon.

25:08.000 --> 25:11.000
You're going to prison.

25:11.000 --> 25:18.000
You can talk about the holes in the AOL there.

25:18.000 --> 25:20.000
Chapter 4.

25:20.000 --> 25:24.000
Prison 888.

25:24.000 --> 25:31.000
Commander Zaduk was in his room at the biggest hotel in Kisangani.

25:31.000 --> 25:36.000
Suddenly he heard the phone.

25:36.000 --> 25:38.000
Commander.

25:38.000 --> 25:41.000
Someone said very quietly.

25:41.000 --> 25:44.000
A man and a woman.

25:44.000 --> 25:52.000
From ship OM45 in prison 888.

25:52.000 --> 25:55.000
The phone went dead.

25:55.000 --> 26:02.000
Zaduk put the phone down, stood up and left his room.

26:02.000 --> 26:10.000
Prison 888 was a big white building without windows near Gog's house.

26:10.000 --> 26:13.000
There were a lot of guards at the gate.

26:13.000 --> 26:18.000
And some more guards marched past the building.

26:18.000 --> 26:22.000
All the guards carried guns.

26:22.000 --> 26:28.000
Commander Zaduk walked across the road to the prison.

26:28.000 --> 26:31.000
I want to visit someone.

26:31.000 --> 26:35.000
My name is Commander Zaduk.

26:35.000 --> 26:37.000
I'm sorry, Commander.

26:37.000 --> 26:41.000
A guard said, we can't open the gate.

26:41.000 --> 26:45.000
Nobody can go in without a letter from Earth Commander.

26:45.000 --> 26:49.000
That's all right, Zaduk said.

26:49.000 --> 26:53.000
And walked along the road past the prison.

26:53.000 --> 26:56.000
A guard ran behind him.

26:56.000 --> 26:58.000
Excuse me, Commander.

26:58.000 --> 27:00.000
He said quickly.

27:00.000 --> 27:02.000
Please come back tonight.

27:02.000 --> 27:06.000
I can open the back gate at midnight.

27:06.000 --> 27:13.000
You can see the two people from ship OM45.

27:13.000 --> 27:15.000
Zaduk looked at the guard.

27:15.000 --> 27:18.000
Your captain is going to kill you.

27:18.000 --> 27:21.000
The guard smiled.

27:21.000 --> 27:27.000
My captain phoned you about the two people from OM45.

27:27.000 --> 27:32.000
He's the brother of Captain Seru.

27:32.000 --> 27:35.000
Zaduk didn't smile.

27:35.000 --> 27:41.000
The prison commander is going to kill you and your captain.

27:41.000 --> 27:43.000
It doesn't matter.

27:43.000 --> 27:47.000
The guard said, we want to help.

27:47.000 --> 27:54.000
Midnight, Zaduk said, and walked away.

27:54.000 --> 28:00.000
At midnight, there were four guards at the front gate of prison 888.

28:00.000 --> 28:05.000
And there was one guard at the back gate.

28:05.000 --> 28:10.000
The guard opened the gate and Zaduk went in.

28:10.000 --> 28:14.000
The guard said nothing.

28:14.000 --> 28:19.000
They walked downstairs into a big room.

28:19.000 --> 28:23.000
A lot of prisoners slept on the floor because there were no beds.

28:23.000 --> 28:26.000
There were no beds or chairs.

28:26.000 --> 28:32.000
Kia and Rilla sat on the floor near the door.

28:32.000 --> 28:35.000
You can talk for five minutes.

28:35.000 --> 28:39.000
The guard said quietly.

28:39.000 --> 28:44.000
The next guard arrives at 1215.

28:44.000 --> 28:47.000
Kia and Rilla stood up.

28:47.000 --> 28:52.000
Good evening, Commander, they said.

28:52.000 --> 28:55.000
Zaduk looked at the prisoners.

28:55.000 --> 28:58.000
Why are all these people here?

28:58.000 --> 29:01.000
He said to Kia and Rilla.

29:01.000 --> 29:05.000
They're in prison because Gog doesn't like them.

29:05.000 --> 29:07.000
I talked to Gog about rain.

29:07.000 --> 29:13.000
I talked to him about the AOL, but he never listens.

29:13.000 --> 29:20.000
Today, someone told me about some fires in the new forest here in Africa.

29:20.000 --> 29:25.000
But Gog doesn't want to hear about those fires.

29:25.000 --> 29:28.000
Zaduk laughed angrily.

29:28.000 --> 29:33.000
And he doesn't want to hear about my trees in Australia.

29:33.000 --> 29:36.000
He never listens to me.

29:36.000 --> 29:43.000
He's always thinking about Mars, not about our beautiful planet Earth.

29:43.000 --> 29:47.000
Kia listened carefully.

29:47.000 --> 29:50.000
Take it easy, Commander.

29:50.000 --> 29:55.000
He said quietly, please talk to Adai.

29:55.000 --> 29:57.000
Adai wants to help.

29:57.000 --> 30:01.000
He can come back from the moon and help you.

30:01.000 --> 30:07.000
Now, Zaduk said, I found Adai this afternoon.

30:07.000 --> 30:10.000
He's a good man and he wants to help.

30:10.000 --> 30:12.000
But I don't need help.

30:12.000 --> 30:15.000
I'm going to stop Gog.

30:15.000 --> 30:19.000
I'm going to kill him.

30:19.000 --> 30:23.000
Kia closed his eyes for a minute.

30:23.000 --> 30:26.000
Gog's guards have guns.

30:26.000 --> 30:30.000
They can kill you, Commander, he said.

30:30.000 --> 30:33.000
You need more people to help.

30:33.000 --> 30:35.000
Wait for Adai.

30:35.000 --> 30:39.000
He can help you to look for more people.

30:39.000 --> 30:44.000
Now, Kia, Zaduk said quietly,

30:44.000 --> 30:47.000
I don't want more people.

30:47.000 --> 30:51.000
Adai can come back to Earth after Gog is dead.

30:51.000 --> 30:54.000
After I'm dead, perhaps.

30:54.000 --> 30:58.000
I don't want Adai to die, too.

30:58.000 --> 31:02.000
Excuse me, Commander, the guard said.

31:02.000 --> 31:05.000
He looked at the clock near the door.

31:05.000 --> 31:08.000
Okay, let's go.

31:08.000 --> 31:11.000
Zaduk said to the guard.

31:11.000 --> 31:14.000
He looked at Rilla and then at Kia.

31:14.000 --> 31:17.000
His eyes were very blue.

31:17.000 --> 31:21.000
Goodbye, he said.

31:21.000 --> 31:25.000
Goodbye, Commander, Kia said.

31:25.000 --> 31:29.000
Be careful, Rilla cried.

31:29.000 --> 31:34.000
And good luck.

31:34.000 --> 31:39.000
Early that morning, Earth Commander's house was quiet.

31:39.000 --> 31:42.000
A guard opened the door.

31:42.000 --> 31:46.000
Good morning, Commander Zaduk, he said.

31:46.000 --> 31:49.000
Earth Commander isn't in his office.

31:49.000 --> 31:52.000
That's all right, Zaduk said.

31:52.000 --> 31:55.000
I can wait.

31:55.000 --> 31:59.000
Zaduk went upstairs and waited.

31:59.000 --> 32:04.000
At eight o'clock, Bell came into the room.

32:04.000 --> 32:08.000
Good morning, Commander, she said.

32:08.000 --> 32:10.000
You're early this morning.

32:10.000 --> 32:13.000
Are you happier today?

32:13.000 --> 32:17.000
Earth Commander was fairly angry with you yesterday.

32:17.000 --> 32:23.000
Don't begin talking about the rain or the AOL today.

32:23.000 --> 32:28.000
Zaduk smiled, but his blue eyes were cold.

32:28.000 --> 32:31.000
No, he said.

32:31.000 --> 32:36.000
I'm not going to talk about rain today.

32:36.000 --> 32:40.000
Just then, Gog came into the room.

32:40.000 --> 32:43.000
He looked at Zaduk.

32:43.000 --> 32:45.000
What's wrong?

32:45.000 --> 32:50.000
Why are you here at eight o'clock in the morning?

32:50.000 --> 32:54.000
Zaduk took his gun from his pocket.

32:54.000 --> 32:58.000
Gog saw the gun and his face went white.

32:58.000 --> 33:02.000
His eyes were dark and afraid.

33:02.000 --> 33:07.000
For a second, nobody moved.

33:07.000 --> 33:13.000
Suddenly, Bell's black and white cat ran into the room.

33:13.000 --> 33:16.000
God's! God's!

33:16.000 --> 33:18.000
Bell shouted.

33:18.000 --> 33:25.000
The cat jumped at Zaduk, and Zaduk hit the cat away from him.

33:25.000 --> 33:31.000
Bell ran across the room to Gog, and Zaduk, at that second,

33:31.000 --> 33:33.000
shot at Gog.

33:33.000 --> 33:36.000
But Bell was between him and Gog.

33:36.000 --> 33:41.000
She gave a cry and fell to the floor.

33:41.000 --> 33:46.000
Her hair looked very red on the black floor.

33:46.000 --> 33:49.000
No, Gog cried.

33:49.000 --> 33:52.000
You shot the Bell!

33:52.000 --> 33:59.000
Three guards ran into the room with their big guns and stood in front of Gog.

33:59.000 --> 34:01.000
Kill him!

34:01.000 --> 34:07.000
Gog shouted and began to help Bell.

34:07.000 --> 34:12.000
Zaduk looked at the guards and then at Bell and Gog.

34:12.000 --> 34:14.000
Kia was right.

34:14.000 --> 34:17.000
He was going to die.

34:17.000 --> 34:20.000
I'm sorry, Kia.

34:20.000 --> 34:22.000
I'm sorry, Adai.

34:22.000 --> 34:25.000
He said quietly.

34:25.000 --> 34:29.000
The guards shot Zaduk.

34:29.000 --> 34:35.000
Slowly, he fell to the floor.

34:35.000 --> 34:38.000
Chapter 5

34:38.000 --> 34:42.000
Forest Fires

34:42.000 --> 34:48.000
Later that morning, four guards took Rilla to Gog's office.

34:48.000 --> 34:54.000
His face looked tired, and his eyes were red.

34:54.000 --> 34:58.000
Leave us, he said to the guards.

34:58.000 --> 35:01.000
Then he looked at Rilla.

35:01.000 --> 35:04.000
Tell me about Kia.

35:04.000 --> 35:07.000
When did you first meet him?

35:07.000 --> 35:10.000
Is Zaduk his friend?

35:10.000 --> 35:13.000
What do they talk about?

35:13.000 --> 35:18.000
Rilla looked down at the floor and said nothing.

35:18.000 --> 35:21.000
Come on, tell me.

35:21.000 --> 35:24.000
Gog said angrily.

35:24.000 --> 35:29.000
He waited, but Rilla said nothing.

35:29.000 --> 35:32.000
Tell me about Zaduk then.

35:32.000 --> 35:36.000
Your father and commander Zaduk were friends.

35:36.000 --> 35:41.000
Now, you're talking to Zaduk about the AOL.

35:41.000 --> 35:43.000
I know that.

35:43.000 --> 35:46.000
What is Zaduk saying?

35:46.000 --> 35:51.000
Why? Why do you want to know about Commander Zaduk?

35:51.000 --> 35:54.000
Rilla asked.

35:54.000 --> 35:57.000
I'm asking the questions, not you.

35:57.000 --> 35:59.000
Gog said.

35:59.000 --> 36:03.000
Did you see Zaduk yesterday?

36:03.000 --> 36:08.000
The AOL is important, not Commander Zaduk.

36:08.000 --> 36:11.000
Rilla said.

36:11.000 --> 36:15.000
Gog watched Rilla carefully.

36:15.000 --> 36:18.000
Zaduk is dead.

36:18.000 --> 36:20.000
No!

36:20.000 --> 36:22.000
Rilla cried.

36:22.000 --> 36:25.000
He is dead.

36:25.000 --> 36:27.000
Gog said again.

36:27.000 --> 36:32.000
You lost your friend here in this building early this morning.

36:32.000 --> 36:36.000
My guards shot him.

36:36.000 --> 36:39.000
Rilla's face went white.

36:39.000 --> 36:41.000
What happened?

36:41.000 --> 36:43.000
Tell me.

36:43.000 --> 36:46.000
I'm going to tell you one thing.

36:46.000 --> 36:48.000
Gog said angrily.

36:48.000 --> 36:52.000
I'm going to destroy Australia.

36:52.000 --> 36:57.000
I'm going to burn Zaduk's new forest there.

36:57.000 --> 37:00.000
You can tell all your friends.

37:00.000 --> 37:06.000
Zaduk wanted to kill me, but I killed him.

37:06.000 --> 37:11.000
He wanted money for rain, money for the AOL.

37:11.000 --> 37:14.000
And now he's dead.

37:14.000 --> 37:19.000
You can tell all those prisoners in Prison 888.

37:19.000 --> 37:24.000
They wanted to stop me, but they can't now.

37:24.000 --> 37:27.000
I'm going to Mars.

37:27.000 --> 37:31.000
Bell always wanted to go to Mars.

37:31.000 --> 37:35.000
He began to hit the table with his hand.

37:35.000 --> 37:39.000
I'm going to leave this dead planet.

37:39.000 --> 37:42.000
Nobody can stop me.

37:42.000 --> 37:46.000
You're crazy, Rilla said.

37:46.000 --> 37:52.000
You killed Zaduk, but one day someone is going to kill you.

37:52.000 --> 37:55.000
Gog stood up.

37:55.000 --> 37:58.000
His face was tired and he looked ill.

37:58.000 --> 38:02.000
Be quiet, he said.

38:02.000 --> 38:05.000
The guards take her away.

38:05.000 --> 38:08.000
Back to 888.

38:08.000 --> 38:13.000
The guards came in and took Rilla out.

38:13.000 --> 38:15.000
What happened?

38:15.000 --> 38:17.000
She asked them.

38:17.000 --> 38:20.000
Commander Zaduk is dead.

38:20.000 --> 38:24.000
Why is Gog angry?

38:24.000 --> 38:27.000
The guards said nothing.

38:27.000 --> 38:31.000
But after they returned to the gate of 888,

38:31.000 --> 38:35.000
a guard said to Rilla very quietly,

38:35.000 --> 38:38.000
Bell is dead.

38:38.000 --> 38:42.000
Zaduk didn't shoot Gog, but he shot Bell

38:42.000 --> 38:46.000
before the guards shot him.

38:46.000 --> 38:49.000
A guard took Rilla into the prison

38:49.000 --> 38:53.000
and soon she was with Keir again.

38:53.000 --> 38:55.000
What happened?

38:55.000 --> 38:58.000
Keir asked, tell me.

38:58.000 --> 39:03.000
Rilla put her hands over her face and began to cry.

39:03.000 --> 39:06.000
Zaduk is dead.

39:06.000 --> 39:08.000
She began.

39:08.000 --> 39:11.000
He didn't kill Gog.

39:11.000 --> 39:15.000
He killed Bell before the guards shot him.

39:15.000 --> 39:21.000
And now Gog is going to destroy Australia.

39:21.000 --> 39:25.000
Keir sat down on the floor next to Rilla.

39:25.000 --> 39:28.000
His face was sad.

39:28.000 --> 39:30.000
Don't cry.

39:30.000 --> 39:34.000
He said quietly.

39:34.000 --> 39:39.000
Three or four prisoners came across the room.

39:39.000 --> 39:41.000
What's the matter?

39:41.000 --> 39:43.000
They asked.

39:43.000 --> 39:45.000
Zaduk is dead.

39:45.000 --> 39:50.000
Keir said, but Bell is dead too.

39:50.000 --> 39:52.000
What's going to happen next?

39:52.000 --> 39:58.000
Someone asked, but nobody answered.

39:58.000 --> 40:03.000
The next afternoon, Captain Seru's brother

40:03.000 --> 40:08.000
took Keir and Rilla to a little room at the back of the prison.

40:08.000 --> 40:12.000
They sat down, and five minutes later,

40:12.000 --> 40:15.000
Captain Seru arrived.

40:15.000 --> 40:18.000
Nobody smiled.

40:18.000 --> 40:21.000
You are right, Captain.

40:21.000 --> 40:23.000
Keir said.

40:23.000 --> 40:29.000
Gog sent us to prison because we told him about the holes in the AOL.

40:29.000 --> 40:32.000
Seru smiled.

40:32.000 --> 40:36.000
You were right, Keir, she said.

40:36.000 --> 40:39.000
Those satellite numbers were very bad.

40:39.000 --> 40:45.000
I began to tell Gog, but he didn't listen to me.

40:45.000 --> 40:49.000
Would you like some coffee and some sandwiches?

40:49.000 --> 40:51.000
Seru's brother asked.

40:51.000 --> 40:54.000
Yes, please, Seru said.

40:54.000 --> 40:57.000
I'm hungry.

40:57.000 --> 41:00.000
She looked at Keir and Rilla.

41:00.000 --> 41:03.000
Things are very bad.

41:03.000 --> 41:05.000
What's happening?

41:05.000 --> 41:07.000
Rilla asked.

41:07.000 --> 41:11.000
You know about Zaduk and Bell?

41:11.000 --> 41:15.000
Yes, Gog told Rilla yesterday.

41:15.000 --> 41:17.000
Keir said.

41:17.000 --> 41:22.000
Seru smiled, but her eyes were not happy.

41:22.000 --> 41:26.000
Gog talked to me this morning, she said.

41:26.000 --> 41:30.000
Her brother came in with the coffee and sandwiches,

41:30.000 --> 41:33.000
and Seru began to eat.

41:33.000 --> 41:39.000
Gog wants to know about Zaduk and about you, she said.

41:39.000 --> 41:45.000
He's going to kill us all, I think, before he goes to Mars.

41:45.000 --> 41:49.000
Suddenly, Rilla felt ill.

41:49.000 --> 41:53.000
I can't eat now, she cried.

41:53.000 --> 41:57.000
But she took some coffee and began to drink.

41:57.000 --> 42:00.000
Let's get out of here, she said.

42:00.000 --> 42:06.000
Perhaps we can get a plane to Brazil and go to my family.

42:06.000 --> 42:09.000
Difficult, Seru said.

42:09.000 --> 42:13.000
Last night, fires began in the new forest in Europe,

42:13.000 --> 42:16.000
and they're moving across Europe.

42:16.000 --> 42:20.000
The fires in Africa are burning fast.

42:20.000 --> 42:26.000
Gog began to destroy Zaduk's forest in Australia yesterday.

42:26.000 --> 42:28.000
Did you phone a die?

42:28.000 --> 42:30.000
Keir asked.

42:30.000 --> 42:32.000
A die?

42:32.000 --> 42:35.000
You never stopped talking about a die.

42:35.000 --> 42:37.000
What can he do?

42:37.000 --> 42:38.000
Rilla said.

42:38.000 --> 42:41.000
She felt angry.

42:41.000 --> 42:44.000
Seru looked at Rilla for a minute.

42:44.000 --> 42:48.000
Yes, I phoned a die before I came here.

42:48.000 --> 42:53.000
I told him about Zaduk and Bell and about the fires.

42:53.000 --> 42:56.000
He asked about you, Keir.

42:56.000 --> 42:59.000
He can't come down at Kiss and Garnie Airport,

42:59.000 --> 43:03.000
because Gog is there with a lot of his guards.

43:03.000 --> 43:08.000
Ship Marsfall is nearly ready and Gog is watching it.

43:08.000 --> 43:13.000
He wants to leave Earth tomorrow.

43:13.000 --> 43:15.000
How can a die help us?

43:15.000 --> 43:17.000
Rilla asked.

43:17.000 --> 43:21.000
He can't shoot all the guards here.

43:21.000 --> 43:24.000
Captain Seru finished the last sandwich.

43:24.000 --> 43:28.000
Let's leave that to a die, she said.

43:28.000 --> 43:31.000
We can do nothing.

43:31.000 --> 43:34.000
Are you going to stay here?

43:34.000 --> 43:36.000
Keir asked.

43:36.000 --> 43:39.000
Yes, Seru answered.

43:39.000 --> 43:45.000
A die is coming to the prison after he arrives on Earth.

43:45.000 --> 43:49.000
Oh yes, Rilla said tiredly.

43:49.000 --> 43:51.000
But when?

43:51.000 --> 43:55.000
Gog can kill us before a die comes.

43:55.000 --> 43:57.000
No, he can't.

43:57.000 --> 44:00.000
Seru's brother said.

44:00.000 --> 44:04.000
You can stay here in this room.

44:04.000 --> 44:07.000
Gog's guards are all afraid.

44:07.000 --> 44:11.000
Afraid of the fires, afraid of the people.

44:11.000 --> 44:16.000
They aren't going to look for you here.

44:16.000 --> 44:18.000
Chapter 6.

44:18.000 --> 44:21.000
Spaceship to the moon.

44:21.000 --> 44:24.000
And so they waited.

44:24.000 --> 44:26.000
And waited.

44:26.000 --> 44:29.000
Rilla slept in her chair.

44:29.000 --> 44:33.000
Keir and Seru talked quietly.

44:33.000 --> 44:36.000
Seru's brother came and went.

44:36.000 --> 44:41.000
Most of the prison guards ran away with the prisoners.

44:41.000 --> 44:47.000
Seven or eight people, some prisoners and some guards,

44:47.000 --> 44:49.000
didn't want to run away.

44:49.000 --> 44:54.000
So they came into the room and waited too.

44:55.000 --> 44:57.000
Ten o'clock came.

44:57.000 --> 44:59.000
Then eleven o'clock.

44:59.000 --> 45:02.000
It was very quiet.

45:02.000 --> 45:06.000
Seru walked up and down the room.

45:06.000 --> 45:09.000
Keir sat next to Rilla.

45:09.000 --> 45:14.000
Seru's brother came into the room again.

45:14.000 --> 45:18.000
It's after midnight, he said.

45:18.000 --> 45:23.000
Just then, they heard the noise of a plane.

45:23.000 --> 45:25.000
Keir stood up.

45:25.000 --> 45:27.000
Come on, he said.

45:27.000 --> 45:31.000
Let's get out of the building.

45:31.000 --> 45:34.000
Quietly, they left the building.

45:34.000 --> 45:38.000
It was a dark, hot night.

45:38.000 --> 45:41.000
There were no guards in front of the prison,

45:41.000 --> 45:45.000
so they went to the gate and waited there.

45:45.000 --> 45:49.000
Suddenly, they saw the plane.

45:49.000 --> 45:56.000
It was a little plane, and it came down on the road in front of the prison.

45:56.000 --> 45:59.000
Rilla took Keir's hand.

45:59.000 --> 46:02.000
You were right, she said.

46:02.000 --> 46:04.000
I'm sorry.

46:04.000 --> 46:07.000
Keir smiled.

46:07.000 --> 46:10.000
He began to feel happy.

46:10.000 --> 46:14.000
That's all right, I understand.

46:14.000 --> 46:19.000
I know I die very well, and you don't.

46:19.000 --> 46:24.000
The plane stopped, and someone opened the door.

46:24.000 --> 46:27.000
Keir ran across to the plane.

46:27.000 --> 46:30.000
How many can you take, he called?

46:30.000 --> 46:33.000
There are twelve of us.

46:33.000 --> 46:36.000
That's all right, someone said.

46:36.000 --> 46:39.000
Quickly, the spaceship is waiting.

46:39.000 --> 46:42.000
The twelve people got into the little plane,

46:42.000 --> 46:45.000
and the plane began to move.

46:45.000 --> 46:49.000
Rilla looked at the captain of the plane.

46:49.000 --> 46:52.000
He was tall with brown hair.

46:52.000 --> 46:54.000
He looked nice.

46:54.000 --> 46:58.000
Was this the famous commander or die?

46:58.000 --> 47:00.000
Where is the spaceship?

47:00.000 --> 47:02.000
Keir asked.

47:02.000 --> 47:06.000
At the old airport, the man said,

47:06.000 --> 47:11.000
One of the fires is moving very quickly across the new forest.

47:11.000 --> 47:18.000
It's going to arrive at the west of Kisangarni before tomorrow, I think.

47:18.000 --> 47:22.000
But the old airport is okay.

47:22.000 --> 47:27.000
Then the man looked at Keir and smiled warmly.

47:27.000 --> 47:30.000
My brother, he said,

47:30.000 --> 47:36.000
My little brother in prison 888.

47:36.000 --> 47:40.000
Your brother, commander or die?

47:40.000 --> 47:42.000
Rilla asked.

47:42.000 --> 47:45.000
But you didn't tell me that?

47:45.000 --> 47:47.000
Keir smiled.

47:47.000 --> 47:50.000
Nobody knew, he said.

47:50.000 --> 47:54.000
But now, it doesn't matter now.

47:54.000 --> 47:58.000
Everyone can know.

47:58.000 --> 48:04.000
The little plane came down at the old airport, south of the town.

48:04.000 --> 48:06.000
Let's be careful,

48:06.000 --> 48:08.000
Adai said.

48:08.000 --> 48:12.000
We don't want someone to shoot us before we leave.

48:12.000 --> 48:15.000
The spaceship was dark.

48:15.000 --> 48:23.000
Quickly, everyone jumped down from the plane and ran across to the spaceship.

48:23.000 --> 48:26.000
Soon, the spaceship left Earth,

48:26.000 --> 48:31.000
and everyone looked down at the burning planet.

48:31.000 --> 48:35.000
They saw the dark smoke of Africa.

48:35.000 --> 48:43.000
And here and there, through the smoke, the red, angry fires.

48:43.000 --> 48:50.000
The fires are destroying the forest very quickly, Saru said.

48:50.000 --> 48:54.000
Adai put his hand on Keir's arm.

48:54.000 --> 48:59.000
I'm sorry about Zadak, he said.

48:59.000 --> 49:03.000
I wanted him to wait, Keir said.

49:03.000 --> 49:07.000
I wanted him to talk to you.

49:07.000 --> 49:10.000
Adai's face was sad.

49:10.000 --> 49:16.000
He didn't want me to die, he said quietly.

49:16.000 --> 49:22.000
He was a good man, and now he's dead.

49:22.000 --> 49:27.000
And Gog is going to Mars, Saru said.

49:27.000 --> 49:30.000
Mars, he's crazy.

49:30.000 --> 49:36.000
Mars isn't ready for people, Adai said.

49:36.000 --> 49:42.000
But Gog wants to go, and so he's going, Saru said.

49:42.000 --> 49:45.000
Tell us about the moon colony.

49:45.000 --> 49:49.000
That isn't ready, you need more money.

49:49.000 --> 49:53.000
No, I don't, Adai said.

49:53.000 --> 49:56.000
The moon colony is ready.

49:56.000 --> 50:00.000
I asked for more money because of Zadak.

50:00.000 --> 50:05.000
I wanted to give him money for rain, but Gog didn't listen.

50:05.000 --> 50:11.000
He wanted all Earth's money for the spaceship to Mars.

50:11.000 --> 50:14.000
I don't want to leave Earth.

50:14.000 --> 50:16.000
Rilla said sadly.

50:16.000 --> 50:20.000
She felt tired and afraid.

50:20.000 --> 50:24.000
Adai smiled warmly at Rilla.

50:24.000 --> 50:28.000
Nobody wants to leave Earth, he said.

50:28.000 --> 50:32.000
But under the moon is the best home for us now.

50:32.000 --> 50:35.000
Wait and see.

50:35.000 --> 50:40.000
The moon colony is a beautiful, wonderful country

50:40.000 --> 50:50.000
with rivers and rain, forests and flowers, buildings and the first town.

50:50.000 --> 50:57.000
You can visit Earth again soon and bring more people to the moon colony.

50:57.000 --> 51:02.000
We all want to help Earth because it's our first home.

51:02.000 --> 51:04.000
I know that.

51:04.000 --> 51:12.000
At the same time, you are going to be happy under the moon.

51:12.000 --> 51:15.000
Suddenly someone cried.

51:15.000 --> 51:19.000
Look at the moon!

51:19.000 --> 51:25.000
And through the window of the spaceship, they saw the moon before them,

51:25.000 --> 51:29.000
cold, white and beautiful.

51:29.000 --> 51:32.000
And under the moon,

51:32.000 --> 51:35.000
there was the moon colony.

